Reasoning: 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security): The paper focuses on developing a secure model for authenticating IIoT components, which falls under the domain of cryptography and security.
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The paper discusses the use of 5G networks for secure authentication of IIoT devices, which is related to networking and internet architecture.
- cs.SE (Software Engineering): The paper may involve software engineering aspects in developing the authentication system for IIoT devices.
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing): The paper may involve distributed computing aspects in developing a flexible and secure model for authenticating IIoT components.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper may involve control systems aspects in evaluating the performance of multiparty authentication in 5G IIoT environments.
